cs.DS, cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.NE 

The paper deals with the problem of approximate nearest neighbor searching, which is a fundamental problem in computer science and is studied in several subfields such as data structures (cs.DS), information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and networked and online algorithms (cs.NE). The paper provides theoretical analysis of the performance of hypercube LSH, which is a variant of locality-sensitive hashing (LSH) used for approximate nearest neighbor searching. Therefore, it is likely to be relevant to these subfields.
